ce:section.ce:para:
Biochemical methane potential tests were performed using a batch AcoD system (
                           Fig. S2
                        ) and the daily biogas yield was determined via a liquid displacement method. The AcoD devices were mainly composed of three parts: anaerobic digestion bottle (digestion site), gas collecting cylinder (collecting biogas), and water collecting bottle (measuring the volume of biogas produced). The anaerobic digestion bottles with an effective working volume of 400 mL were maintained at mesophilic conditions (36 ± 1 °C) through a constant temperature device. Each part was sealed by a rubber plug and connected with a rubber tube through a glass tube. More experimental details could be found in the previous works (Jia et al., 2020; Yun et al., 2019).
